snippet: Tornadoes rolled in from the prairie and slammed Oklahoma City and its suburbs on Friday, killing five people, the Oklahoma medical examiner’s office said.
abstract: Tornadoes hit Oklahoma City and its suburbs, killing five people and injuring 50 more.
lead_paragraph: Tornadoes rolled in from the prairie and slammed Oklahoma City and its suburbs on Friday, killing five people, the Oklahoma medical examiner’s office said.

headline.main: Oklahoma: 5 Killed and 50 Injured in Tornado
